Compiled by Venessa Miemis:



==PROJECTS:==

- Open Mesh Project - http://www.openmeshproject.org/ - building a mesh network for Egypt
- Open Source Mesh - http://opensourcemesh.org/index.htm - group looking at how to build a reliable open source meshing software
- B.A.T.M.A.N. - http://www.open-mesh.org/ - better approach to mobile ad-hoc networking; routing protocol for multi-hop ad-hoc mesh networks
- Roofnet - http://pdos.csail.mit.edu/roofne... - 802.11b/g mesh network in development at MIT CSAIL
- GNUnet - https://gnunet.org/ - framework for secure p2p networking that doesn not use any centralized or otherwise trusted services
- Dot-P2P - http://dot-p2p.org/index.php?tit... - a free, decentralized, and open DNS system
- SMesh - http://www.smesh.org/ - seamless wireless mesh network being developed at John Hopkins University
- Coova - http://coova.org/ - open source software access controller for captive portal (UAM) and 802.1X access provisioning
- Babel - http://www.pps.jussieu.fr/~jch/s... - a loop-free distance-vector routing protocol for IPv6 & IPv4
- SolarMESH - http://owl.eng.mcmaster.ca/~todd... - solar powered IEEE 802.11 wireless LAN mesh network  and relaying infrastructure solution
- WING - http://www.wing-project.org/ - wireless mesh network for next-generation internet; partially built on Roofnet
- Daihinia - http://daihinia.com/ - a tool for WiFi; turns a simple ad-hoc network into a multi-hop ad-hoc network
- P2P DNS - http://p2pdns.baywords.com/ - building a distributed p2p DNS system
- Digitata - https://sites.google.com/a/opens... - developing an inexpensive infrastructure (low bandwidth internet terminals) for basic internet exposure to children in African countries 
- Netsukuku - http://netsukuku.freaknet.org/ - an ad-hoc netowork that uses only WiFi connectivity and a specifically-built adddress system that allows direct communications between machines without resorting to the HTTP protocol
- Tonika - http://pdos.csail.mit.edu/~petar... - open source organic network project; administration-free platlform for large-scale open-membership (social) networks with robust security, anonymity, resilience and performance guarantees

Updates:

* Village Telco (http://villagetelco.org) : "We make the Mesh Potato, an Open Source, Open Hardware mash-up of a mesh WiFi access point and an analogue telephony adaptor (ATA) which means you can build a telephone and Internet network at the same time."

* The world of Ham Radio is also into mesh networking, using OLSR.  See http://hsmm-mesh.org/ for those efforts.

==COMMUNITIES:==

- We Rebuild - http://p2pfoundation.net/We_Rebuild - cluster of net activists who have joined forces to collaborate on issues concerning access to a free internet without intrusive surveillance
- Freifunk - http://global.freifunk.net/ - non-commercial initiative for free wireless networks, in english here
- Athens Wireless Metropolitan Network - http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ath... - grassroots wireless community in Greece
- Wireless community networks by region - http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lis... - list on wikipedia
- wlan ljubljana (in slovenian) - http://wlan-lj.net/ - open wireless network in ljubljana
- The Darknet Plan - http://www.reddit.com/r/darknetp... - reddit thread dedicated to organizing anad creating a decentralized VPN as the first stage of the darknet plan
- the connective - http://theconnective.net/fire/ - Q&A for a citizen-owned internet


